from sklearn import datasets, linear_model
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, ConfusionMatrixDisplay, roc_curve, RocCurveDisplay
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import time
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.preprocessing import PolynomialFeatures
import warnings

warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')
noise = 16
seed = 244823
samples = 2423
loop = 100

def normalize(x):
    return (x-np.min(x))/(np.max(x)-np.min(x))

def sigmoid(z):
  return 1.0 / (1 + np.exp(-z))

def cm(ytest, ypred, title, showplot=True,):
    cm = confusion_matrix(ytest, ypred)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(ytest, ypred).ravel()
    cm[0,0] = tp
    cm[1,0] = fp
    cm[0,1] = fn
    cm[1,1] = tn

    sensitivity = tp/(tp+fn)
    specificity = tn/(tn+fp)
    balacc = (sensitivity+specificity)/2
    f1score = 2*(sensitivity*specificity)/(specificity+sensitivity)

    if showplot:
        cm = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(confusion_matrix=cm)
        cm.plot(cmap='binary')
        plt.title(title)
        plt.show()
    return sensitivity, specificity, balacc, f1score

def roc(ytest, ypredicted, title):
    fpr, tpr, tresholds = roc_curve(ytest, ypredicted)
    rocowanie = RocCurveDisplay(fpr=fpr, tpr=tpr)
    rocowanie.plot()
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel('1 - specificity')
    plt.ylabel('Sensitivity')
    plt.show()

def kontur(xx, yy, theta, xtrain, ytrain, ifPolynomial=False):
    zzz = np.c_[xx.flatten(), yy.flatten()]
    if ifPolynomial:
        zzz = poly.fit_transform(zzz)
    zzz = np.c_[np.ones([len(xx.flatten()), 1]), zzz]

    predict = sigmoid(zzz @ theta)
    predict = [1 if x >= 0.5 else 0 for x in predict]
    predict = np.asarray(predict).reshape(xx.shape)

    # plt.ylim(0,0.7)
    plt.title('Classification of analytical model')
    plt.contourf(xx, yy, predict, alpha=0.4)
    plt.scatter(xtrain[:, 0], xtrain[:, 1], c=ytrain)
    plt.show()

def sklkontur(xx, yy, Z, xtrain, ytrain):
    Z = Z.reshape(xx.shape)
    plt.contourf(xx, yy, Z, alpha=0.4)
    plt.scatter(xtrain[:,0], xtrain[:,1], c=ytrain)
    # plt.ylim(xtrain.min(),xtrain.max())
    # plt.xlim(xtrain.min(),xtrain.max())
    plt.title('Classification of skl model')
    plt.show()

def sklmodel(xtrain,ytrain,xtest,returnTime=False):
    global endtimeskl, Z

    if returnTime == True:
        start = time.time()
        for i in range(loop):
            model = linear_model.LogisticRegression()
            model.fit(xtrain, ytrain)
            model.predict(xtest)
            model.predict(np.c_[xx.ravel(), yy.ravel()])
        endtimeskl = (time.time() - start)/loop

    model = linear_model.LogisticRegression(max_iter=10000)
    model.fit(xtrain, ytrain)
    ypredforcm = model.predict(xtest)
    if xtrain.shape[1] == 2:
        Z = model.predict(np.c_[xx.ravel(), yy.ravel()])
    return model.decision_function(xtest), ypredforcm

def analyticalmodel(krok, xtrain, xtest, ytrain, returntime=False):
    lr = 10000
    global endtimeanal
    xtrain = np.c_[np.ones((xtrain.shape[0],1)),xtrain]
    xtest = np.c_[np.ones((xtest.shape[0],1)),xtest]
    ytrain = ytrain.reshape(len(ytrain),1)
    theta = np.ones([xtrain.shape[1], 1])

    if returntime:
        start = time.time()
        for i in range(loop):
            for i in range(lr):
                z = sigmoid(xtrain @ theta)
                deltatheta = ((-krok*(z-ytrain)*(1-z)*z).T @ xtrain).T
                theta = theta + deltatheta
            wynik = xtest @ theta
        endatimenal = (time.time() - start)/loop

    for i in range(lr):
        z = sigmoid(xtrain @ theta)
        deltatheta = ((-krok*(z-ytrain)*(1-z)*z).T @ xtrain).T
        theta = theta + deltatheta
    wynik = xtest @ theta
    predict = [1 if x >= 0.5 else 0 for x in wynik]
    return wynik, predict, theta

def windsorize(dataframe):
    for i in dataframe.columns:
        if dataframe[i].dtype == 'float64':
            q3, q1 = np.percentile(dataframe[i], [75, 25])
            iqr = q3 - q1
            lowerbound = q1 - 1.5*iqr
            upperbound = q3 + 1.5*iqr
            dataframe.loc[dataframe[i] < lowerbound, i] = lowerbound
            dataframe.loc[dataframe[i] > upperbound, i] = upperbound

def normalize2(dataframe):
    return (dataframe-dataframe.min())/(dataframe.max()-dataframe.min())

windsorize(australia)

xtrainglobal, xtestglobal, ytrainglobal, ytestglobal = train_test_split(australia, raintomorro, stratify=raintomorro, test_size=0.2, train_size=0.8, random_state=seed)

def preprocess(x,y):
    x.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)
    y.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)

    y = y.to_numpy()

    y = pd.DataFrame(le.fit_transform(y.ravel()))
    y.rename(columns={0: 'RainTomorrow'}, inplace=True)

    columnscat = ['WindGustDir', 'WindDir9am', 'WindDir3pm', 'RainToday', 'Month',]
    columnfloat = ['MinTemp', 'MaxTemp', 'Rainfall', 'WindGustSpeed', 'WindSpeed9am', 'WindSpeed3pm', 'Humidity9am', 'Humidity3pm', 'Pressure9am', 'Pressure3pm', 'Temp9am', 'Temp3pm']

    scaled = normalize2(x[columnfloat])
    encoding = pd.DataFrame(onehot.fit_transform(x[columnscat]))

    encoding.columns = onehot.get_feature_names_out()

    australiaprocessed = pd.concat([scaled, encoding], axis=1)
    australiaprocessed = pd.concat([x['Location'], australiaprocessed], axis=1)
    australiaprocessed = pd.concat([australiaprocessed, y], axis=1)
    return australiaprocessed
trainingprocessed = preprocess(xtrainglobal,ytrainglobal)
